---
description: Prepare a structured ATM handoff summary before ending your session.
---

1. Run `node atm.mjs next --prompt "<current user prompt>" --json` for user-requested task work; use `node atm.mjs next --json` only as read-only orientation.
2. Summarize what was completed this session (files changed, tests run, evidence captured).
3. List what remains: open tasks, blockers, and their ATM error codes if any.
4. Do not leave tasks in `in-progress` state without a handoff note in the task card.
5. Unlock all locks you hold before ending the session.
